  "text": "Wear-leveling techniques strive to distribute write traffic among different cells uniformly. Row-Shifting and Segment swapping [CITATION_1] ] balances writes across each row and among segments, and Start-Gap [Qureshi et al. 2009b] tries to balance writes across the entire memory. [CITATION_2] propose a swap-based algorithm for wear-leveling. [CITATION_3] take into account the endurance variation effect, and balances the wear rates instead of wear traffic of cells across the memory.",
